1.title: The Scoop
1.plot: When Starfire becomes obsessed with an ice cream scoop, the others try to teach her that inanimate objects can't replace people.

2.title: Chicken in the Cradle
2.plot: In the season five premiere, Beast Boy neglects his responsibilities, leaving the other Titans to raise his baby chick.

3.title: Kabooms - Part 1
3.plot: The Titans are excited to see the movie version of their favorite show, "Babies vs. Dogs" until the movie's exposition makes watching it super-boring. In order to save the film, the Titans go into the movie and break up the talk with exciting action.

4.title: Kabooms - Part 2
4.plot: Inspired by the "Babies vs. Dogs" movie, the Titans set out to make a big Hollywood film of their own.

5.title: Tower Renovation
5.plot: Following the destruction of their tower by Slade, the Titans go house hunting.

6.title: My Name is Jose
6.plot: Raven gives the Titans new super powers, but they have a hard time adjusting.

7.title: The Power of Shrimps
7.plot: Aqualad uses shrimp and prime rib to win back Raven.

8.title: Monster Squad!
8.plot: The Titans want to be the scariest trick-or-treaters in town, so Raven casts a spell to turn them into real monsters.

9.title: Real Orangins
9.plot: This week an all new episode of Teen Titans Go!.

14.title: Justice League's Next Top Talent Idol Star: Second Greatest Team Edition - Part 2
14.plot: When he isn't invited to Beast Boy's birthday party, Robin throws his own party, with special guest Bob Uecker.

1.title: Legendary Sandwich
1.plot: Raven sends the Titans on a quest to find ingredients for a magical sandwich.

2.title: Pie Bros
2.plot: Cyborg's birthday is coming up, and Beast Boy takes a job at their favorite pie shop so he can afford an expensive gift. But when he has to work during Cyborg's party, his job threatens to come between the two pie bros.

3.title: Driver's Ed
3.plot: Robin takes driver's ed, and his teacher has some tricks up his sleeve; Raven's dad cozies up to her friends in hopes of luring her over to the dark side.

4.title: Dog Hand
4.plot: Raven's demon dad, Trigon, comes to visit, and wins over her friends in an effort to get her to embrace dark magic and become evil like him.

5.title: Double Trouble
5.plot: Cyborg has Raven create doubles of himself and Beast Boy.; To go on a date with Starfire, Robin kidnaps Speedy.

6.title: The Date
6.plot: Robin gets up the courage to ask Starfire on a date, only to find that she has already agreed to go out with Speedy, Robin's arch-rival...so Robin kidnaps Speedy!

7.title: Dude, Relax!
7.plot: The Titans try to get Robin to relax after his uptight nature starts affecting the other members of the team. In the second part, chores around the Tower aren't getting done and each Titan blames the other members for the mess.

8.title: Laundry Day
8.plot: Nobody wants to wash the Titans' gross dirty uniforms. Raven volunteers, using her magic, which brings the uniforms to life and turns them against the Titans.

9.title: Ghostboy
9.plot: Beast Boy pretends to be a ghost haunting Starfire so she will do his bidding. When she figures out the ruse, she and the other Titans convince Beast Boy that he's actually dead.

10.title: La Larva Amor
10.plot: The gang agrees to take on the responsibility of babysitting Silkie, but they end up losing the slimy little fellow who ends up in Mexico, having an exciting telenovella adventure.

11.title: Hey Pizza!
11.plot: Beast boy and Cyborg find that a pizza place has a policy that says if it's not delivered by a certain time it's free. They try every way they can think of to slow down the delivery person, but things aren't as easy as they thought.

12.title: Gorilla
12.plot: Beast Boy turns into a loud, obnoxious gorilla and refuses to change back, driving Robin crazy. Gorilla Beast Boy takes over the leadership of the Titans, which leads to chaos.

13.title: Girl's Night Out
13.plot: Robin, Beastboy and Cyborg decide to have a crazy Boys' Night Out without Starfire. Starfire brings Raven along to break Jinx out of jail to have a Girl's Night Out ; Beast Boy's indecisiveness causes him to be fired from the Teen Titans and the Teen Titans have to find a replacement Titan member, ranging from Vixen, B'wana Beast, Detective Chimp, and the Wonder Twins.

14.title: You're Fired
14.plot: Beast Boy's poor job performance leads to his being fired from the Titans. After auditioning possible replacements, they hire a pair of shape-shifting twins to take Beast Boy's place.

15.title: Super Robin
15.plot: Envious of the other Titans' powers, Robin convinces Raven to use her magic to give him powers, despite her warnings that it could ruin his life.

16.title: Tower Power
16.plot: Cyborg shorts out when he gets wet, so the others disassemble him to dry. When they can't figure out how to reassemble him, they upload Cyborg into the Tower's main computer.

17.title: Parasite
17.plot: Starfire is infected by a sentient, telepathic parasite. Robin panics over the situation but learns many valuable lessons.

18.title: Starliar
18.plot: When Starfire is the only Titan invited to the Titans East Annual Dance Party, Beast Boy teaches her how to lie so that she can spare the other Titans' feelings - but her lies turn all of the Titans against each other.

19.title: Meatball Party
19.plot: While trying to entice Raven into joining a meatball party, Cyborg fires a half-meat, half-robot mystery meatball into her mouth, cracking her tooth and releasing the demon octopus that lives in her mouth.

20.title: Staff Meeting
20.plot: Robin's beloved staff is broken by the other Titans, so he goes on a perilous quest to the ancient Universe Tree to find a new magic staff to replace it.

21.title: Terra-ized
21.plot: Beast Boy thinks the villainess Terra is his new girlfriend, but she is just using him to gain access to all of the Titans' secrets. Only Raven suspects Terra, but the others just think that Raven is jealous.

22.title: Artful Dodgers
22.plot: The Titans confidently expect to win an upcoming dodgeball championship, even though the only thing they ever practice is their victory dance. Then they come up against an unbeatable dodge ball team - the H.I.V.E.

23.title: Burger vs. Burrito
23.plot: Cyborg and Beast Boy are in perfect sync, except when it comes to their taste in food. What's the best food ever created, burgers or burritos? The two friends have an all-out competition to settle things once and for all.

24.title: Matched
24.plot: Cyborg's Love Matcher 5000 program pairs Raven with Beast Boy and Starfire with Aquaman. While Beast Boy does everything he can to get Raven to love him, Robin tries to be more like Aquaman to win Starfire's heart.

25.title: Colors of Raven
25.plot: A mysterious prism creates five Ravens, each of a different color and with a different aspect of her personality, disrupting life in the Tower.

26.title: The Left Leg
26.plot: Cyborg creates a huge robot powered by all five Titans, each of whom controls a different body part. Robin gripes about being the left leg and makes improvements to his section.

27.title: Books
27.plot: The Titans discover the wonders of reading ... but after opening a book that brings their thoughts to life, they must fight their own imaginations!

28.title: Lazy Sunday
28.plot: Cyborg and Beast Boy love lazy Sundays sitting on the couch ... even when it's a Tuesday! But when Robin replaces the couch with a treadmill, the two lazy teens must embrace the new active lifestyle.

29.title: Starfire the Terrible
29.plot: Starfire turns evil so she can become Robin's arch enemy and make him eligible as the greatest superhero ever.

30.title: Power Moves
30.plot: Robin gets carried away when he and Cyborg start merging their powers and tech into cool Power Moves. He moves into Cyborg's body and refuses to leave.

31.title: Staring at the Future
31.plot: Cyborg and Beast Boy have a staring contest that lasts 30 years, bringing them face to face with a future of adulthood and responsibility - and they hate it.

32.title: No Power
32.plot: Feeling the other Titans depend too much on their super powers, Robin challenges them to go 24 hours without using their powers. To his distress, they all succeed, leading him to question his own value to the team.

33.title: Sidekick
33.plot: Robin gets called to the Batcave, but it is only to be a house sitter while Batman is away. The other Titans show up and tease Robin about his sidekick status.

34.title: Caged Tiger
34.plot: After their "bro-cation" - a vacation just for the bros - Cyborg, Beast Boy, and Robin return closer than ever ... but their bro-mentum is interrupted by Dr. Light. Teen Titans Bro!

35.title: Second Christmas
35.plot: Upset that Christmas is over, Raven, Cyborg and Beast Boy trick Starfire into believing that there is such a thing as a second Christmas with a "second Santa."

36.title: Nose Mouth
36.plot: Raven succumbs to pressure to use her magic to solve problems around the Tower, but becomes more and more evil with each spell.

37.title: Legs
37.plot: After the Titans take away her cloak as a joke, Raven finds it fun to use her legs. Meanwhile, Cyborg becomes dark and sarcastic after Raven's cloak gets stuck on his head.

38.title: Breakfast Cheese
38.plot: Starfire has an epiphany and convinces her fellow Titans to join her in living lives of peace and nonviolence.

39.title: Waffles
39.plot: Cyborg and Beast Boy show their love of waffles by making it the only word they say, much to the annoyance of the other Titans.

40.title: Be Mine
40.plot: Beast Boy helps Terra escape the dimension she was banished to and once again continues his romantic pursuit of her. But Terra only has revenge on her mind and plans to destroy all the Titans on Valentine's Day.

41.title: Opposites
41.plot: Cyborg and Jinx fall for each other and carry on an illicit good/evil romance, even though the Titans and H.I.V.E. disapprove.

42.title: Birds
42.plot: Robin removes two mockingbirds from the chimney with a gas he created in his lab. But the chemicals mutate the birds into muscular bullies who then move into the tower.

43.title: Brain Food
43.plot: Beast Boy is tired of being the least intelligent of the Titans. When all of his efforts to get smart fail, he uses Raven's spell book to cast a spell - not to make himself smarter, but to make all of the other Titans dumber.

44.title: In and Out
44.plot: Robin dresses up as Red X to infiltrate the Hive Five and blow up their headquarters, but the plan changes once Robin discovers how awesome it is there. Soon all the Titans want in the HIVE.

45.title: Little Buddies
45.plot: Tired of being the only one of the Titans without a little buddy sidekick, Cyborg adopts Brother Blood's henchman, PainBot, and sneaks him into the tower. Now Cyborg just has to keep PainBot from harming the other Titans.

46.title: Missing
46.plot: Cyborg, Beast Boy and Robin return Silkie to Killer Moth to collect a cash reward. Starfire is devastated until she sees Killer Moth might love Silkie just as much as she does.

47.title: Uncle Jokes
47.plot: Hoping to learn how to be actually funny - unlike Robin who can only tell "uncle jokes" - Starfire asks to join Cyborg and Beast Boy's twosome. Robin is upset as he feels this throws off the balance of the Tower and goes to the extreme to deal with it.

48.title: Más y Menos
48.plot: Mas y Menos visit the tower to get superhero lessons from Robin. The twins become fast friends with the other Titans, but Robin just wants to focus on the training.

49.title: Dreams
49.plot: After an exciting night of crime fighting, the Titans go to sleep and each one has unique dreams.

50.title: Grandma Voice
50.plot: In order to defeat Mother Mae Eye, Cyborg starts using a grandma voice, but soon that persona takes over and he begins making the other Titans dress warmly and clean their dishes.

51.title: Real Magic
51.plot: Robin starts performing magic tricks after seeing the Amazing Mumbo Jumbo, much to the delight of the other Titans - except Raven, who warns Robin that doing lame tricks will upset the Magic God.

52.title: Puppets, Whaaaaat?
52.plot: Robin makes marionette versions of the other Titans as a way to deal with their lack of respect. However, he takes things a little too far when he wishes the real Titans were more like his puppets and The Puppet Wizard grants his wish.

1.title: Mr. Butt
1.plot: Blackfire pays a surprise visit to her sister Starfire, saying she wants to spend some quality time with her. The other Titans think that Blackfire is playing another trick, but Starfire is sure that this time Blackfire is serious about reviving their sisterly love.

2.title: Man Person
2.plot: Beast Boy is distressed by his big new battle scar, until Cyborg convinces him that the scar makes him look tough and manly. Now Beast Boy wants to look even tougher.

3.title: Pirates
3.plot: Aqualad asks Raven out on a date, which makes Beast Boy jealous. Cyborg tries to prove that Aqualad is really a pirate.

4.title: Money Grandma
4.plot: It's Team Election Day. Robin forgets what being a true leader is, so Raven brings George Washington back to show him what being a true leader is all about.

5.title: I See You
5.plot: When Robin starts a smear campaign against all of the other Titans so that he can be relected Team Leader, Raven uses a time machine to bring a great leader from the past to teach Robin how to lead

6.title: Brian
6.plot: The Titans and the Little Buddies throw a surprise party for Birdarang and Beat Box. When the Titans leave to check out a crime aler t, Cyborg tells the Little Buddies to keep the party going while they're gone. Eight months later, the Titans still haven't returned and the party is still going.

7.title: Nature
7.plot: When Beast Boy loses his ability to change into animals, he realizes that he's lost touch with his wild side. He goes to the forest to reconnect with his inner beast, but Mother Nature isn't as great as he had hoped.

8.title: Salty Codgers
8.plot: Mad Mod steals the youth from Cyborg, Beast Boy, Starfire and Robin, turning them into Raven's favorite type of people: salty codgers. Instead of helping the Titans get their youth back, Raven teaches them how cool old people are.

9.title: Knowledge
9.plot: Starfire is tired of not fitting in with the other Titans, and asks Raven to help her to learn more about human culture.

10.title: Slumber Party
10.plot: When the Titans find out that Cyborg is afraid of the dark, they decide to have a slumber party to help him face his fears.

11.title: Love Monsters
11.plot: Raven warns the other Titans not to go near a box containing the Twin Destroyers of Azarath. Starfire can't help it and opens the box, giving hugs and snuggles to the two tiny, adorable Destroyers ... but love only makes the Destroyers stronger.

12.title: Baby Hands
12.plot: Brother Blood erases the memories of the Titans (sans Robin), giving Robin the opportunity to re-train them to respect him.

13.title: Caramel Apples
13.plot: Trigon arrives to wreck the Earth, but only because his daughter Raven didn't get him anything for Father's Day. Starfire misses the fatherly relationship, so she starts spending time with Trigon.

14.title: Sandwich Thief
14.plot: Someone has stolen Robin's perfect sandwich, and he's on the hunt to find it.

15.title: Friendship
15.plot: Control Freak zaps the Titans into the latest episode of Pretty Pretty Pegasus, and the team has to figure out how to help the Pegasuses in order to get home.

16.title: Vegetables
16.plot: Beast Boy's healthiness persuades the other Titans into becoming vegetarians, but the converts take their new dietary restrictions a little too seriously.

17.title: The Mask
17.plot: There's a reason Robin never takes off his mask.

18.title: Serious Business
18.plot: When Robin rations bathroom time to 5 minutes per visit, the other Titans try to show him the magic of the bathroom.

19.title: Halloween
19.plot: When Halloween comes packaged in the trappings of the modern commercialized world, Raven decides to put the real spirit of Halloween back into Halloween.

20.title: Boys vs. Girls
20.plot: Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy think boys are more superior toward girls. Raven and Starfire convince Cyborg and Beast Boy that girls are better and they immediately turn. So, Robin mutates some cooties to get the other boys back.

21.title: Body Adventure
21.plot: Robin thinks a body adventure would be fun. Well, he was wrong.

22.title: Road Trip
22.plot: When Cyborg fixes up the T-car, he takes the other titans on a road trip, hoping to bond.

23.title: Thanksgiving
23.plot: Robin invites Batman to thanksgiving dinner, but the other titans invited some friends, or more.

24.title: The Best Robin
24.plot: Robin calls on his team of Robins, Batman's other sidekicks, when the other Titans are too lazy to fight crime.

25.title: Mouth Hole
25.plot: Robin goes on a quest to gain a new power: whistling.

26.title: Hot Garbage
26.plot: When the Titans try to get Beast Boy to clean his room, they discover that there's more to garbage than just trash.

27.title: Robin Backwards
27.plot: The Titans decide they should keep an eye on Nibor, the Bizzaro World's Robin, when he arrives in Jump City.

28.title: Crazy Day
28.plot: It is crazy day, and Raven has to try not to be driven crazy by the other Titans.

29.title: Smile Bones
29.plot: Beast Boy and Cyborg teach the other Titans the importance of eating correctly.

30.title: Real Boy Adventures
30.plot: Cyborg asks Raven to make him a real boy again.

31.title: Hose Water
31.plot: When Cyborg and Starfire find a baby bird, it awakens their inner child.

32.title: Let's Get Serious
32.plot: After Young Justice easily takes out the HIVE while the other Titans make silly jokes, Robin decides the team needs to get serious.

33.title: Tamaranian Vacation
33.plot: The Titans visit Starfire's homeworld, Tamaran.

34.title: Rocks and Water
34.plot: Raven and Beast Boy are shocked to discover that their exes, Terra and Aqualad, are now dating each other.

35.title: Multiple Trick Pony
35.plot: Kid Flash wants to join the Titans, but Robin insists that he can't because Flash is just a "one-trick pony."

36.title: Truth, Justice and What?
36.plot: The Teen Titans fight the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles over pizza.

37.title: Two Bumble Bees and a Wasp
37.plot: Robin tries to teach the Titans to respect money, but he ends up as the one who learns the lesson.

38.title: Oil Drums
38.plot: Cyborg wants to have an '80s TV show marathon, but the remote is missing.

39.title: Video Game References
39.plot: Robin sets up a virtual reality room for training purposes, immersing each Titan in their own video game adventure.

40.title: Cool School
40.plot: When Raven chooses to hang out with Rose Wilson, a cool escaped criminal, the other Titans feel left out. To feel "less lame," they decide to go to Cool School.

41.title: Kicking a Ball and Pretending to Be Hurt
41.plot: Robin teaches the Titans how to play soccer. They quickly become obsessed, and accidentally uncover the secret reason why the sport is so popular.

42.title: Head Fruit
42.plot: When Beast Boy's head starts to rattle, Robin suggests that he should find a hobby so that his brain will stop shrinking. Beast Boy and his brain agree to take up gardening.

43.title: Yearbook Madness
43.plot: Beast Boy and Cyborg decide to make a yearbook for the Titans.

44.title: Beast Man
44.plot: Beast Boy realizes he can use his power to turn himself into an adult.

45.title: Operation Tin Man
45.plot: Gizmo convinces the Titans he's kidnapped Cyborg, when in reality Cyborg's just hanging out in the HIVE tower with his girl Jinx. When Gizmo gets annoyed by Cyborg's constant presence, the two start a prank war.

46.title: Nean
46.plot: When Raven insists that she's "nean" - part nice and part mean - Trigon curses her so that she can only be nice, hoping to win her over to the mean side.

47.title: Campfire Stories
47.plot: The Titans are having a terrible time on their camping trip, so Robin suggests that they each tell a scary campfire story.

48.title: And the Award for Sound Design Goes to Rob
48.plot: Raven just wants some peace and quiet for once, and accidentally makes a magical deal that eliminates all sounds.

49.title: The Hive Five
49.plot: The HIVE just wants a day off to relax, but the Titans keep ruining their plans.

50.title: The Return of Slade
50.plot: Beast Boy and Cyborg insist on hiring a clown for a Titans party, even though Robin tells them that clowns are for little kids. When the clown fails to live up to their memories, Cyborg and Beast Boy decide to give the clown some cool updates.

51.title: More of the Same
51.plot: The Titans practice New Year's Eve traditions so that, for once, they can perform them all correctly and have a good rest of the year.

52.title: Some of Their Parts
52.plot: Beast Boy finds a box of cool stuff collected from missions over the years, including the prism that separated Raven into five parts. Robin decides to split each Titan with the prism so he can choose only the best parts for his ideal crime fighting team.

1.title: Cat's Fancy
1.plot: Robin decides to become a cat so that Starfire will finally love him.

2.title: Leg Day
2.plot: After being defeated due to poor leg strength, Raven and the Titans work out their lower bodies and become the League of Legs.

3.title: Dignity of Teeth
3.plot: Beast Boy gets a stack of cash from the Tooth Fairy, so, against Raven's advice, the other Titans start knocking out their own teeth to get some of that sweet Tooth Fairy money.

4.title: Croissant
4.plot: A giant cocoon mysteriously appears in the Titans' living room, and no one can find Beast Boy.

5.title: Spice Game
5.plot: The titans, sans Robin, become addicted to spices.

6.title: I'm the Sauce
6.plot: Stuck inside because of bad weather, the Titans play rainy day games after Robin convinces them that indoor activites will cheer up the clouds and make the rain stop.

7.title: Hey You, Don't Forget About Me in Your Memory
7.plot: Robin convinces the Titans to go back to school with him so he can finally become the all-American class president-type he's dreamed of being.

8.title: Accept the Next Proposition You Hear
8.plot: Robin refuses to give the Titans any more orders so that they'll learn to think for themselves. Instead, the Titans start taking their cues from fortune cookies.

9.title: The Fourth Wall
9.plot: Control Freak informs the Titans that they are on a TV show he created and demands they earn him an award.

10.plot: Cyborg's real strength comes not from his robot parts, but from his favorite song.

11.title: Grube's Fairytales
11.plot: Robin tries to teach the Titans valuable life lessons by reading them fairytales, but the others co-opt his stories and spin them into their own twisted yarns.

12.title: A Farce
12.plot: Brother Blood takes the Titans to trial for their recent destruction of Jump City.

13.title: Scary Figure Dance
13.plot: The Titans' Halloween party is interrupted by the Hive Five robbing a candy factory.

14.title: Animals, It's Just a Word!
14.plot: After the other Titans are injured, Beast Boy donates his blood to save them.

15.title: BBBDAY!
15.plot: It's Beast Boy's birthday! Will the other Titans remember?

16.title: Black Friday
16.plot: Starfire is visited by three ghosts and shown the true meaning of Black Friday.

17.title: Two Parter: Part One/Two Parter: Part Two
17.plot: Robin gets obsessed with creating a double episode

18.title: Two Parter - Part 2
18.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

19.title: The True Meaning of Christmas
19.plot: Fed up with never getting presents from Santa, the Titans head to the North Pole to take themselves off the Naughty List ... by any means necessary.

20.title: Squash & Stretch
20.plot: The Titans learn about cartoon-style violence in order to get revenge on a snack-stealing squirrel.

21.title: Garage Sale
21.plot: Robin makes the other Titans sell their treasured mementos from past episodes.

22.title: Secret Garden
22.plot: When Cyborg starts to rage out, Starfire takes him to her secret garden in the backyard to relax.

23.title: The Cruel Giggling Ghoul
23.plot: The Titans go to an amusement park to see LeBron James (voice guest star LeBRON JAMES) but instead help solve a mystery.

24.title: How 'Bout Some Effort
24.plot: It's Valentine's Day and Cyborg goes to great lengths to make it special for his girlfriend, Jinx.

25.title: Pyramid Scheme
25.plot: Beast Boy starts making tons of cash thanks to a pyramid scheme and convinces the other Titans to join in.

26.title: Beast Boy's St. Patrick's Day Luck and It's Bad
26.plot: The Titans - except for Beast Boy - are cursed on St. Patrick's Day and must travel to the end of the rainbow for the cure.

27.title: The Teen Titans Go Easter Holiday Classic
27.plot: The Easter Bunny is missing, and it's up to the Titans to find him before Easter is ruined.

28.title: Batman v Teen Titans: Dark Injustice
28.plot: The Titans try to outprank each other on April Fools' Day.

29.title: Bottle Episode
29.plot: When the Titans get trapped in a giant bottle in their living room, they pass the time by reminiscing.

30.title: Finally a Lesson
30.plot: Robin finally teaches the other Titans a valuable lesson.

31.title: Arms Race with Legs
31.plot: Lady Legasus battles the League of Legs after her teammates turn evil

32.title: Obinray
32.plot: The Titans start speaking Pig Latin to prevent Robin from eavesdropping.

33.title: Wally T
33.plot: The Titans discover the magic of "fan strength," thanks to their #1 fan, Wally T!

34.title: Rad Dudes with Bad Tudes
34.plot: After seeing a pair of cool dudes on rollerblades, Robin tries to be just like them.

35.title: Operation Dude Rescue - Part 1
35.plot: Female heroes and villains unite to save Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy from The Brain.

36.title: Operation Dude Rescue - Part 2
36.plot: Female heroes and villains unite to save Robin, Cyborg and Beast Boy from The Brain.

37.title: History Lesson
37.plot: Robin tries to teach the Titans valuable history lessons, but the others co-opt his stories and spin them into their own twisted yarns.

38.title: The Art of Ninjutsu
38.plot: This week an all new episode of Teen Titans Go!.

39.title: Think About Your Future
39.plot: The Titans are reckless with their money and health, much to the detriment of their future selves.

40.title: TTG v PPG
40.plot: When Mojo Jojo shows up in Jump City, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and the Teen Titans to take him down.

41.title: Coconut Cream Pie
41.plot: When the Titans find themselves shipwrecked on a deserted, they must use the island's resources to survive

42.title: Pure Protein
42.plot: Still shipwrecked on the deserted island, the Titans try to find food, but stumble upon dinosaurs instead.

43.title: Open Door Policy
43.plot: Still shipwrecked on the deserted island, the Titans decide to hold a team competition, but first they'll have to avoid the Alien Hunter!

44.title: Crazy Desire Island
44.plot: Robin grants crazy wishes for The Titans

45.title: The Titans Show
45.plot: When the Titans try to get off the deserted island, they soon realize that everything is not as it seems.

46.title: Booty Scooty
46.plot: In order to save Titans Tower from some wealthy land developers, the Titans search for pirate treasure.

47.title: Who's Laughing Now
47.plot: Upon finding his first armpit hairs, Beast Boy excitedly embarks on a journey to find his spirit animal, joining a literal fraternity of bears.

48.title: Oregon Trail
48.plot: The Titans get into the "Pioneer Spirit" as they head west on the Oregon Trail.

49.title: Snuggle Time
49.plot: When yet another crime alert interrupts their relaxation, the Titans decide to become villains so that they can do whatever they want.

50.title: Oh Yeah

imdb.title: Teen Titans Go!
plot: Superhero roommates Robin, Cyborg, Starfire, Raven and Beast Boy love saving the day, but what happens when they're done fighting crime?::Cartoon Network
synopsis: This slapstick animation focus on what the young superheroes Robin, Beast Boy, Cyborg, Starfire and Raven do between their battles - whether it be having a staff meeting or Robin learning to drive a car.
